Print an Indicator Map Object

Source: R/print_methods.R
print.indicator_map.Rd

Provides a summary representation of an indicator_map object, designed for user-friendly display in the console.

Usage

# S3 method for indicator_map
print(x, n = 10, ...)

Arguments

x

An indicator_map object.

n

Integer specifying the number of rows of data to display.

...

Additional arguments.

Examples

library(sf)
#> Linking to GEOS 3.10.2, GDAL 3.4.1, PROJ 8.2.1; sf_use_s2() is TRUE
obs_rich_map <- obs_richness_map(example_cube_1)
print(obs_rich_map)
